headline: Front-Month Gold Closes Down for Second Week
summary: Front-month gold futures rose for the day, but ended down 0.7% to $2,638.60 an ounce for the week, marking the second straight weekly decline.

headline: Battle for 7-Eleven Could Be Tipping Point for Japanese M&A
summary: The multibillion takeover battle is unfolding against a backdrop of heightened deal activity involving foreign bidders, fanned by a weak yen, undervaluation, and a profitability gap at many big Japanese firms compared with their international peers.
